So please use only water, wet/dry paper towel to wipe fruits off.
snippet.textOriginal: Agree with all, *except* washing the fruit with soap is NOT good, and NOT recommended by FDA, even in these times. Thanks for this video. Anyone watching this needs to heed your words. I'm recovering from this wretched virus. An idiot in a store queue stood before me was very tall and coughing everywhere, over his shopping and the conveyer belt.
Though sanitising my hands before and after shopping in store, washing my hands before and after unpacking my groceries there were microbes on them. Dr told me I've escaped lightly. I've various auto immune disorders. Please please listen to this advice. This virus is still with me 13 days after falling sick. In the U.K. delivery drivers have to stay 2 metres away from you. Consider asking delivery drivers to do that. We're being asked to put out bags/ boxes for them to put our groceries in. Think ahead. Stay safe.

snippet.textDisplay:
Nice vid, perhaps a tad compulsive but this doc's points are technically valid, namely that one can bring in groceries whose surfaces are contaminated by the ChiCom Virus.

I'm sure the author knows by now that the 17-day cruise-ship evidence was for the presence of RNA, likely scraps of no longer-infectious viral genome.

Envelope viruses like the ChiCom Virus are actually fairly fragile... so we're back to we don't really know how long to fret about the potential infectiousness of virus-contaminated fomites... but it's likely not all that long, esp if you live where the air is dry -- envelope viruses are thought to dry-out and then fall apart fairly easily. And temps greater than 170F will "kill" it.
Keep your distance, keep your hands clean, keep your hands off your face -- the last may turn out to be the most important precaution.
Thanks again Doc!

snippet.textDisplay: I used to work in housekeeping at a hospital.We were trained to fold our cloths in half,and then in half again so that every time you wiped a possibly contaminated section you flip your cloth.That gives you 4 separate areas on each side of the cloth,then you flip it to the opposite side for a total of 8 clean sections to work with .I hope that makes sense. I don't mean this as a criticism .Just something I remember that may be helpful.Thank you.I appreciate your video. Love from Canada ♥

Went yesterday and bought a huge grocery order, seeing this today brings tears of joy to my eyes - it took forever - but we did all of these things !! Fruit and vegetables in their own bath - the table cleaned and ready to unload and disinfect our goods on. I'm not a fearful person, but going to do that grocery to do the shopping was unnerving. I'm so glad to see that we did these things as we should have. Oh, and I was the only person to go into the stores - had to go to the pharmacy as well as the grocery store and I was the designated shopper. It's no time for social outings !!
Thank you for this video - I will be sharing :D
